-- Insurer Travelers profit up 6 percent as investment income rises
-- 
-- Tue Oct 21, 2014 07:07AM EDT
-- None



Oct 21 (Reuters) - Property and casualty insurer Travelers Cos Inc <TRV.N> reported a 6 percent rise in quarterly net profit, helped by higher net investment income and a fall in disaster-related losses.

The company, a Dow Jones Industrial Average <.DJI> component, said net income rose to $919 million, or $2.69 per share, in the third quarter ended Sept. 30, from $864 million, or $2.30 per share, a year earlier. [ID:nBwc1frV8a]